   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Quickstart\n",
    "-------------\n",
    "\n",
    "Here is how to fit a simple likelihood function:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[snowline]     from: [0.55272749 0.57041427]\n",
      "[snowline]     error: [0.04 0.04]\n",
      "Maximum likelihood: L = -0.0 at:\n",
      "    Hinz                0.5000 +- 0.0100\n",
      "    Kunz                0.5000 +- 0.0100\n",
      "[snowline] Initiating gaussian importance sampler\n",
      "[snowline]     sampling 400 ...\n",
      "[snowline]     sampling efficiency: 100.000%\n",
      "[snowline] Optimizing proposal (from scratch) ...\n",
      "[snowline]     running variational Bayes ...\n",
      "[snowline]     reduced from 9 to 1 components\n",
      "[snowline] Importance sampling 400 ...\n",
      "[snowline] Likelihood function evaluations: 1252\n",
      "[snowline] Status: Have 792 total effective samples, done.\n",
      "\n",
      "logZ = -11.985 +- 0.003\n",
      "\n",
      "    Hinz                0.500 +- 0.010\n",
      "    Kunz                0.4995 +- 0.0098\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "paramnames = ['Hinz', 'Kunz']\n",
    "\n",
    "def loglike(z):\n",
    "    return -0.5 * (((z - 0.5) / 0.01)**2).sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "def transform(x):\n",
    "    return 10. * x - 5.\n",
    "\n",
    "from snowline import ReactiveImportanceSampler\n",
    "\n",
    "sampler = ReactiveImportanceSampler(paramnames, loglike, transform)\n",
    "\n",
    "sampler.run()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This gave us error estimates and even logZ!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",

      "Loglikelihood was called 1252 times.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Loglikelihood was called %d times.\" % sampler.results['ncall'])"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "\n",
    "paramnames = ['Hinz', 'Kunz'] #, 'Fuchs', 'Gans', 'Hofer']\n",
    "\n",
    "def loglike_rosen(theta):\n",
    "    a = theta[:-1]\n",
    "    b = theta[1:]\n",
    "    return -2 * (100 * (b - a**2)**2 + (1 - a)**2).sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "def transform_rosen(u):\n",
    "    return u * 20 - 10\n",
    "\n",
    "sampler = ReactiveImportanceSampler(paramnames, loglike_rosen, transform=transform_rosen)\n",
    "sampler.run(min_ess=1000, max_ncalls=1000000)\n"
   ]

    {
     "data": {

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "x = np.linspace(-0.5, 4, 100)\n",
    "a, b = np.meshgrid(x, x)\n",
    "z = -2 * (100 * (b - a**2)**2 + (1 - a)**2)\n",
    "\n",
    "g = plots.get_single_plotter()\n",
    "g.plot_2d(mcsamples, paramnames)\n",
    "plt.contour(a, b, z, [-3, -2, -1], cmap='Reds')\n",
    "plt.xlim(-0.5, 2)\n",
    "plt.ylim(-0.5, 4);"
   ]
  },
